He said, "The composer knows what he wants.
It's all in the music.
Sing it then! "
His tactical technique was absolutely clear and precise, but it was neither dictatorial nor majestic.
No matter where the standard was, he always raised it.
John Frayn Turner writes:
If a conductor was to be knighted, it was Vernon Handley.
I knew him well for two decades when he conducted the Guildford Philharmonic from 1962 to 1982.
I have reviewed more than 100 of his concerts over the past 40 years and I can honestly say that I have never been disappointed by any of them - and I have been inspired many times.
