"They are completely healthy" and "no ransom has been paid to the hijackers," Egypt's tourism minister Zohejr Garrana said on the runway of the airport.
Since their capture on Sept. 19 during a four-wheel drive safari at the foot of Mount Uanat, on the borders of Egypt, Sudan and Libya, a group of hostages have been dragged from one hideout to another by 35 unknown hijackers.
